  "notes": "HAR-245 records the live Shopify 2026-04 metaobject schema-change lifecycle: definition create, row create/update/delete before schema update, definition update with added required field, removed field, field order reset, displayNameKey change, validation change, and publishable capability disable, then row validation/add/update/delete after the schema edit. Captured behavior shows `resetFieldOrder` is an update-input field, not a top-level mutation argument; `MetaobjectFieldDefinitionUpdateInput` does not expose `type`; omitted publishable status defaults to DRAFT while the capability is enabled; pre-existing rows read the new required display field as null and fall back to a handle-derived displayName until updated; rows missing a required display field are omitted from immediate catalog reads. The pre-schema catalog branch is excluded from strict comparison because the live Admin search index had not materialized the newly active row immediately, while local staging intentionally exposes supported writes immediately."
}
